# API Schema Conventions

## Database
- Location: `backend/data/pos.db` (SQLite via Drizzle ORM)
- Schema: `backend/src/db/schema.ts`
- Migrations: `backend/src/db/migrate.ts` (runs on API startup)

## Multi-Tenant Authorization
Every store-scoped table must enforce membership via middleware:

- `requireStoreMember` — any member can read/create
- `requireManager` — manager or owner for updates
- `requireOwner` — owner only (store settings, team management)

## Table Rules
- Immutable records: `orders`, `order_items`, `inventory_transactions` — no PATCH/DELETE routes
- Unique constraints: `(store, order_number)`, `(store, product)` for inventory, `(store, user)` for store_members
- All business tables have `store` FK to `stores`

## Adding a New Entity
1. Add Drizzle table in `backend/src/db/schema.ts` + migration in `migrate.ts`
2. Add Hono routes under `/api/stores/:storeId/...`
3. Add Dexie table + indexes in `frontend/app/lib/db.ts`
4. Add TypeScript interface in `frontend/app/lib/types/index.ts`
5. Register in sync engine's `getTable()` map and delta sync endpoint

## File Uploads
- Stored at `backend/data/uploads/{collection}/{recordId}/{field}.{ext}`
- DB stores relative path (e.g. `products/abc123/image.webp`)
- Served by Nginx at `/uploads/` (not through API)
